Definition: In this task you will be given a list of integers. You should round each integer to the nearest tens place. That means you should round the number to the nearest multiple of 10.

Positive Examples.explanation: The output correctly rounds each integer in the input list to the nearest ten. So this is a good example.
The integers '-66' and '-74' both round to '-70' because that is the closest multiple of 10 for each integer. So this is a good example.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output rounded every integer to the incorrect multiple of 10. So this is a bad example.
The output rounded all of the negative numbers to the incorrect multiple of ten. So this is a bad example.
The output rounded to the correct 10 places but removed the hundreds digit from the input numbers. So this is a bad example.
